\date{2024-04-25}
\taxon{proposition}
\author{eigil-rischel}
\p{
    Let #{f: V \to \RR} be convex, so that #{(V,*,f)} is a minmax problem.
    Then we can form the modified minmax problem #{L = (V,V^*,(x,\alpha) \mapsto f(x) - \alpha(x))} - note that, up to a sign change in the domain, this amounts to adding the constraint #{x = 0}.
}
\p{
    Then #{(L^*)^+ = -L^- = f^*}
}